creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 143 by Various.
Read in English by Winston Tharp; Shakira Searle; Ian King; Tony Scheinman; Leara Morris-Clark; Phil Schempf; Larry Wilson; Raymond Cockle; Elise C. Boucher; Bruce Kachuk; Newgatenovelist; Gemma L Myers; Son of the Exiles; Algy Pug; Chris Pyle
This is a collection of 29 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for April 2015. This collection includes: Aedh Wishes for the Cloths of Heaven, by William Butler Yeats Sonnet VIII - And you as well must die, beloved dust, by Edna St. Vincent Millay April, by Elizabeth Clementine Kinney A Ballade of an Anti-Puritan, by G. K. Chesterton Because I could not stop for Death, by Emily Dickinson Dirge, by Alfred Kreymborg An Elegy on the Death of a Mad Dog, by Oliver Goldsmith Fidessa, Sonnet 37, by Bartholomew Griffin Fitchburgh, by Caroline A. Mason Green Grow the Rashes, by Robert Burns High-tide, by Jean Starr Untermeyer Houses of Dreams, by Sara Teasdale I'm Nobody! Who are you?, by Emily Dickinson The Last Charge, by Oliver Wendell Holmes, Sr. Less than the Dust, by Laurence Hope The Library, by Caroline A. Mason To A Little Invisible Being Who Is Expected Soon to Become Visible, by Anna Laetitia Barbauld The Lovers, by C. J. Dennis An Old Master, by C. J. Dennis Our Limitations, by Oliver Wendell Holmes, Sr. The Pantheist's Song of Immortality, by Constance Naden Questions and Answers, by Oliver Wendell Holmes, Sr. The Sadness of the Moon, by Charles Baudelaire The Sledge at The Gate, by Richard Henry Stoddard Song Of A Second April, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Sonnet 97, by William Shakespeare To the Unattainable, by Laurence Hope When Lilacs Last in the Dooryard Bloom’d, by Walt Whitman Written in Early Spring, by William Wordsworth For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
